  <li><strong>Recognize Malolactic vs. Steel-Fermented Styles</strong> - The best Chardonnays fall into distinct camps: malolactic-fermented wines (creamy, buttery) versus stainless steel/neutral oak examples (mineral-driven, crisp). Top Chablis producers like Vincent Dauvissat use minimal malolactic conversion, preserving acidity and terroir expression, while Meursault producers embrace full malolactic for richness. Know which style you prefer before purchasing.</li>

